---
import { site } from '../config';
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Lumecon"
  description="Privacy Policy for Lumecon and its family of platforms: Local Economic Impact, Tribal Economic Impact, and Global Economic Impact. Covers data collection, use, retention, and Cedar AI handling."
  canonical="https://lumecon.ai/privacy"
  keywords="Lumecon privacy policy, data privacy, economic impact analysis privacy, Cedar AI privacy, tribal economic data privacy, IMPLAN, RIMS II, REMI, BEA RIMS, Cornell University"
>
  <h1 class="hl-block hl-block--gold-b">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <div class="date">Being prepared by legal counsel</div>
  <p>
    The Privacy Policy for Lumecon and its family of platforms (Local Economic Impact, Tribal
    Economic Impact, and Global Economic Impact) is being prepared.
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy will cover data collection, use, sharing, analytics, retention, and your rights with
    respect to personal information provided through Lumecon's websites and services, including
    Cedar&trade;.
  </p>
  <h2 class="legal-subhead">Analytics &amp; your consent</h2>
  <p>
    Analytics are off by default. We use privacy-friendly product analytics only after you opt in
    through the consent banner, to understand which parts of the site are useful and to improve
    them. If you decline, or until you choose, no analytics or tracking scripts run, no analytics
    cookies are set, and no usage beacon is sent. You can change your mind by clearing this
    site&rsquo;s data in your browser, which brings the banner back.
  </p>
  <p>
    Lumecon does not sell personal information. When analytics are enabled they are scoped to
    product improvement, not advertising.
  </p>
  <div class="note">
    <strong>Counsel:</strong>
    {site.counsel}<br />Contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="note-link">{site.email}</a>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
